main event: Two witnesses reported seeing a silvery object with a pointed nose in Alexandria, Virginia, on March 13, 1967, for a duration of 45 minutes.
interesting points: The object was observed for 45 minutes with no reported sounds., The object was described as silvery with a pointed nose and an upside-down painted cup on it., Witnesses noted the object disappeared quickly, speeding off to the right., The conclusion of the report stated that there was insufficient data for evaluation., A sketch of the object was included in the report.
sighted object: a silvery object with a pointed nose
